-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Mon Dec 08, 2014 11:16PM EST
-- None



Dec 9 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Honda Motor Co <7267.T> will expand an investigative recall of vehicles with air bag inflators made by Takata Corp <7312.T> globally, a person familiar with the matter said. [ID:nL3N0TT02W]  * German financial watchdog Bafin has found no indication that Deutsche Bank AG <DBKGn.DE> co-Chief Executive Anshu Jain was aware or part of possible attempts at the German lender to manipulate interest rates, a source familiar with Bafin's probe said. [ID:nL6N0TS2ZA]  * Royal Bank of Scotland Plc <RBS.L> has launched the sale of private bank Coutts International and has invited at least 10 potential suitors, including Credit Suisse Group AG <CSGN.VX>, Julius Baer <BAER.VX> and Malayan Banking Bhd <MBBM.KL> to participate in an auction, sources said. [ID:nL3N0TP29L]  * BMW AG <BMWG.DE> supervisory board will meet on Tuesday and discuss top-level appointments and strategy at the German carmaker, two sources told Reuters on Monday. [ID:nL6N0QA2K5]  * JCDecaux SA <JCDX.PA>, the world's biggest outdoor advertising group, is exploring a bid for the European advertising assets of U.S. rival Clear Channel Outdoor Holdings Inc <CCO.N>, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL1N0TS1WB]  * Private equity firm Abris Capital Partners has rejected a bid from Poland's BOS Bank <BOSP.WA> for its FM Bank PBP, two sources with knowledge of the bidding process said, leaving three other bidders still in the race. [ID:nL6N0TS2S8]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]